{
  "title": "ISic001274. I.Sicily inscription 001274",
  "body": "<div id=\"editions\"><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Giorgia Capra; edition source: <a href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/Q2SBPG9F\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/Q2SBPG9F</a></div><div id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <a id=\"al1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]K[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>] <br id=\"al2-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"divine\" data-text=\"Δημήτηρ\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Δημήτηρ\">Δημήτηρ</span></span> ἡ <span data-text=\"ἱερ\">ἱερ</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>] </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Giorgia Capra; edition source: <a href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/Q2SBPG9F\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/Q2SBPG9F</a></div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\"><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><a id=\"al1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]K[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<br id=\"al2-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"divine\" data-text=\"Δημήτηρ\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Δημήτηρ\">ΔΗΜΗΤΗΡ</span></span>Η<span data-text=\"ἱερ\">ΙΕΡ</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]</span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span><span>Text of Gualtherus</span></span>; </li><li><span class=\"2\">2: <span>Franz suggests: Δήμητρ[ι] ἱερ[όν]</span></span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2> translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\">  </p><p>  </p></div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p>Only seen by Gualtherus, and while Franz' amendment is attractive, it is difficult to see how exactly that is recovered from Gualtherus' transcription. Tortorici suggests that the inscription may not be genuine, a result of antiquarian enthusiasm to attribute the ruins as the temple, although this would be a relatively early date for such invention.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li> Gualtherus 1624 [1625] no.31 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931</a></li><li> Amico 1741 236 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002186\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002186</a>  </li><li> Castelli 1769 cl.1, no.20 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084</a>  </li><li> Castelli 1784 cl.1, no.22 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083</a>  </li><li> Franz 1853 5649e <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250</a></li><li> Kaibel 1890 <a href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">449</a>  <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072</a></li><li> Tortorici 2016 65 </li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"> Line 1    Interlineation line 1 to 2    </div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. </div>",
